# =============================================================================
# Model Metadata for OpenCode Configuration
# =============================================================================
#
# This file contains display names and context limits for GGUF models.
# Used by setup.sh and sync-opencode.sh to generate OpenCode config.
#
# FORMAT:
#   model_id|display_name|context_limit|output_limit
#
# NOTES:
#   - model_id must match the model ID in models.conf (including quant suffix)
#   - Unknown models will use defaults (32768 context, 8192 output)
#   - Display names appear in OpenCode's model selector
#   - Lines starting with # are ignored
#   - Add new models here when you add them to models.conf
#
# =============================================================================
# CHEATSHEET
# =============================================================================
#
# PARAMETER COUNT:
#   1-3B   - Small models, fast but limited capability
#   7-8B   - Good balance for consumer GPUs (8-12GB VRAM)
#   13-14B - Better quality, needs 12-16GB VRAM
#   30-32B - High quality, needs 24GB+ VRAM
#   70B+   - Best quality, needs 48GB+ VRAM or multi-GPU
#
# CONTEXT LIMITS (how much text the model can "see"):
#   4096   - Very limited, basic chat only
#   8192   - Small tasks, simple questions
#   16384  - Medium tasks, single file editing
#   32768  - Standard for most models (recommended default)
#   65536  - Large tasks, multi-file context, agentic coding
#   128000 - Very large context (Llama 3.1, some Qwen models)
#
# OUTPUT LIMITS (max tokens per response):
#   4096   - Short responses, quick answers
#   8192   - Standard responses (recommended default)
#   16384  - Long responses, code generation, agentic tasks
#   32768  - Very long outputs (rarely needed)
#
# VRAM vs CONTEXT (estimates - varies by model size):
#   8GB VRAM  -> 8192 context max, smaller models only
#   12GB VRAM -> 8192-16384 context
#   16GB VRAM -> 16384-32768 context
#   24GB VRAM -> 16384-32768 context (65536 with smaller models)
#   48GB+ VRAM -> 32768-65536+ context
#
# QUANTIZATION SUFFIXES:
#   q4km  - 4-bit quantization, good balance of quality/size
#   q3km  - 3-bit quantization, smaller but lower quality
#   q5km  - 5-bit quantization, better quality, larger size
#   q8    - 8-bit quantization, near-original quality
#
# DISPLAY NAME CONVENTIONS:
#   Include model name, size, and purpose hints:
#   "Qwen3 8B Q4KM (Fast)"        - General purpose, speed focused
#   "DeepSeek-R1 32B (Reasoning)" - Shows thinking process
#   "Qwen2.5-Coder 14B (Agentic)" - Optimized for coding tasks
#
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Small/Test Models
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qwen2-0.5b-q4km|Qwen2 0.5B Q4KM (Test)|8192|4096
qwen3-4b-q4km|Qwen3 4B Q4KM (Small)|32768|8192

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Autocomplete Models (for IDE code completion)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qwen2.5-coder-3b-q4km|Qwen2.5-Coder 3B Q4KM (Autocomplete)|32768|8192

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# General Purpose Models
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qwen3-8b-q4km|Qwen3 8B Q4KM (Fast)|32768|8192
qwen3-14b-q4km|Qwen3 14B Q4KM (Balanced)|32768|8192
qwen3-32b-q4km|Qwen3 32B Q4KM (Quality)|32768|8192
qwen3-32b-q3km|Qwen3 32B Q3KM (Less VRAM)|32768|8192
llama3.1-8b-q4km|Llama 3.1 8B Q4KM|128000|8192

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Reasoning Models (show thinking process)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
deepseek-r1-14b-q4km|DeepSeek-R1 14B Q4KM (Reasoning)|32768|8192
deepseek-r1-32b-q4km|DeepSeek-R1 32B Q4KM (Reasoning)|32768|8192
deepseek-r1-32b-q3km|DeepSeek-R1 32B Q3KM (Reasoning)|32768|8192

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Coding Models (optimized for code generation)
# These get higher context/output limits for agentic tasks
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
qwen3-30b-q4km|Qwen3 30B MoE Q4KM (Agentic)|65536|16384
qwen3-30b-q3km|Qwen3 30B MoE Q3KM (Agentic)|65536|16384
qwen2.5-coder-14b-q4km|Qwen2.5-Coder 14B Q4KM|65536|16384
qwen2.5-coder-32b-q4km|Qwen2.5-Coder 32B Q4KM|65536|16384
qwen2.5-coder-32b-q3km|Qwen2.5-Coder 32B Q3KM|65536|16384
